#!/bin/sh
# =============================================================================
# service-event  (SATELLITE / SECONDARY NODE)
#
# Location on router : /jffs/scripts/service-event
# Called by          : Asuswrt-Merlin — before every service event (pre-hook)
#
# Intentionally a no-op. Two reasons:
#
# 1. service-event fires BEFORE Merlin acts, so bridge changes made here get
#    immediately overwritten by Merlin's own restart logic.
#
# 2. On satellites, AiMesh manages wireless through its own internal sync
#    from the root node, bypassing Merlin's service event mechanism entirely.
#    Confirmed via boot-time logging: no wireless events appear in
#    service-event during AiMesh initialisation. The pre-hook cannot
#    intercept wireless init.
#
# Bridge restoration after wireless restarts is handled by service-event-end
# (post-hook), which fires after Merlin completes the restart.
# =============================================================================
